node.text:
Whether you were aware or not, @nickyjam magically got everyone to stand up and dance the entire time during his performance.

What a night watching nearly 10,000 people during the pandemic celebrate and actually have some fun.

If there’s anything America and the world needs today is a bit of value, entertainment and a ton of laughter.

All three were brought during awards ceremony night.
Future looks bright!

node.text:
Last night @dustinpoirier crushed it at the Vault Conference.

At the end of the interview he & his wife @mrsjoliepoirier told us about families in New Orleans who needed 40 generators due to the hurricane.

Within 24 hrs we raised $58,000.

Thanks to everyone who contributed and helped.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Patrick Bet-David in Hakkasan Las Vegas Nightclub with @gabreal42. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text:
Back in 2002 we were at a Christmas party.  One of our relatives casually disrespected my Dad.

I told my Dad we’re leaving the party.  My Dad was upset and embarrassed of me wanting to leave early.

I was furious that a relative whom my Dad helped when he was younger in Iran would have the audacity to speak to my Dad in that manner.

When we got in the car, I looked at my Dad and told him the following.

“Dad, these people will eat their words one day. I PROMISE YOU I will work so hard everyday until the world knows your last name.  They’re gonna have to kill me to stop me from making that a reality. I PROMISE YOU.”

Here was the problem.

In 2002, I was broke with nothing to my name. I was $49,000 in debt.  No one knew me. I was about to go back in the Army because nothing was going my way.

The rest is history.

My Dad has and always will be my #1 hero.  This man changed my life.

That smile in the picture is worth everything.

PS:  just getting warmed up. Future looks bright!

node.text:
Capitalism is the reason why the US leads the world in immigration.

Capitalism is the reason why creative people crush it in Hollywood by coming up with creative ideas.

Capitalism is the reason why we lead the world in innovation and advancement.

Capitalism attracts creative people.

Capitalism attracts independent people.

Capitalism attracts leaders who don’t want to be held down by their government.

Capitalism attracts the best talent.

Capitalism attracts comedians and actors. Even those who hate capitalism. Try being a comedian in China making fun of the leader.

Capitalism exposes those who constantly work to improve themselves and those who waste their time just entertaining themselves.

Capitalism has converted more communistic & socialist countries into capitalism then the other way around.

The idea of capitalism has historically crushed any other economical system.

May capitalists and creatives continue to fight for their freedoms instead of sitting on the sidelines worried about offending those who are experts at complaining and feeling entitled to things they haven’t earned.
